ordinated debt subordinated debt with equity enhancement convertible debentures or equity preferred and common investments are tailored to meet the needs of the specific opportunity investment horizon of up to seven years details subordinated debtmezzanine and equity investments   established companies can optimize their capital structure using a customized subordinated debt or equity investment solution   bmo capital partners typically serves as a key participant within your larger financing solution often working alongside the senior lender our subordinated debt and equity investments are individually structured according to the unique circumstances and needs of your business as a partner in your business our team of professionals commits to give your company the time and attention required to support your needs with our experience expertise and judgment working on your behalf you can be assured of receiving a financial solution designed to provide you with the flexibility and capital needed to help you achieve your goals portfolio   currently our portfolio consists of over  investments in a variety of industries including     business services health services manufacturing and industrial products consumer products a selection of experience  kb  pdf our team   alex baniczky vice president alexbaniczkybmocom   alex is the head of the bmo capital partners and midmarket mergers  acquisitions lines of business with a focus on private equity subordinated debt and ma transactions across canada alex brings over  years of experience in investment project and structured financing alex joined bmo in  and has held a variety of senior level positions within the bmo financial group alex is a member of the institute of chartered accountants of ontario and has a ba honours from queens university at kingston evan bennitt managing director ontario evanbennittbmocom   evan bennitt is a managing director of bmo capital partners and shares responsibility for overseeing investments in ontario evan has more than years of middlemarket leveraged finance experience and prior to joining bmocp led cit’s leveraged finance business in canada evan holds a bachelor of commerce from the university of windsor and is a cfa charter holder dale tingley managing director ontario daletingleybmocom   dale joined bmo capital partners in  and shares responsibility for overseeing investments in ontario and atlantic canada he brings over fifteen years of principal investing experience having invested across a wide variety of industries and transaction types dale began his career at working ventures inc followed by a move to cai capital management in  where he focused on north american midmarket buyouts primarily in aerospace  defense health care services waste management power generation and business services most recently dale was head of investments for aquila infrastructure management dale holds a ba in economics and a diploma of engineering from the university of prince edward island an mba from the schulich school of business and the icdd designation lee grimshaw managing director western canada leegrimshawbmocom   lee grimshaw is a managing director of bmo capital partners and is responsible for overseeing investments in western canada lee has extensive industry and corporate experience in aircraft engines aerospace and appliances in addition to  years of financial services industry experience in subordinated debt equity senior debt cash flow and asset backed transactions lee holds a degree in commerce has an mba in finance and is a cfa charter holder he is also an alumnus of the ge financial management program offices      toronto head office first canadian place  king street west th floor toronto ontario mx a montreal  rue saintjacques rd floor montreal quebec hy l calgary first canadian centre th avenue sw th floor calgary alberta tp n vancouver first bank tower  burrard street th floor vancouver british columbia vx l bmo capital markets corp  new york  ny  